STATUS: PRE-RELEASE — NO LICENSE GRANTED YET

This repository is public so the work can be read, discussed and critiqued while
it is being built. It is **not** open source (yet), and this file exists to remove
the ambiguity that comes from having no license file at all.

WHAT THIS MEANS TODAY

  You MAY: read the code, read the documentation, quote it with attribution,
           open issues, and send feedback or suggestions.

  You MAY NOT: use, copy, modify, redistribute, or create derivative works,
               in whole or in part, for any purpose, without prior written
               permission from the copyright holder.

WHY IT IS NOT OPEN SOURCE YET

An open-source license is effectively irreversible: anything published under a
permissive license stays available under that license for that version, forever.
Choosing one is easy later; un-choosing one is impossible. Since the design is
still moving, the license decision is deliberately deferred rather than guessed.

The intent is to release under an open license once the project stabilises. The
code and the model weights will be licensed separately — they are different kinds
of artifact with different conventions.

FEEDBACK AND COLLABORATION ARE WELCOME

If you want to use any part of this, build on it, or collaborate: ask. The default
answer to a reasonable request is yes. Open an issue on
https://github.com/0Franky/sml and describe what you have in mind.

